# SPA fallbacks for dynamic route trees only. All static public routes AND
# published blog posts are prerendered to real files by
# scripts/prerender-heads.mjs; anything else falls through to 404.html with a
# genuine 404 status.
# Note: the rewrite target must be `/` — `/index.html` is rejected by Pages'
# infinite-loop detection and the whole rule gets ignored.
# Note: there is deliberately NO `/blog/*` rule — _redirects rules take
# precedence over static assets, so a splat here would shadow every
# prerendered per-post file (and rewriting to `<slug>.html` 308s via Pages'
# pretty-URL normalization). Consequence: a post published AFTER the last
# build 404s until the next Pages build (any git push triggers one). Unknown
# blog URLs correctly return 404.
/admin/* / 200
/portal/* / 200

# Legacy URLs from the pre-Aethyx design system (pages removed from the bundle).
# 301 to the closest live equivalent instead of 404ing any residual link equity.
/start-here /intake 301
/membership /services 301
/testimonials /portfolio 301
/seo /services 301
/rebrand /portfolio 301
